				<h2 class="font-headline" style="font-size:clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<p style="color:#64748b; font-size:0.9375rem; margin-top:1rem; max-width:28rem; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">Everything you need to know about NekoBeat.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reveal" style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
				<details>
					<summary>What is NekoBeat?</summary>
					<div>NekoBeat is a free, open-source desktop music aggregator and player for Windows. It lets you search and stream music from YouTube, SoundCloud, and Spotify in one unified interface, with features like offline caching, a 10-band DSP equalizer, synchronized lyrics, and Discord Rich Presence.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Is NekoBeat really free?</summary>
					<div>Yes, completely free. NekoBeat is MIT-licensed open-source software with no ads, no tracking, and no subscription fees. Ever.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Does NekoBeat work offline?</summary>
					<div>Yes! When you "like" a song, it's automatically cached to your local drive. Once cached, you can play it offline with zero latency. The cache persists across app restarts.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>How does NekoBeat compare to Spotify?</summary>
					<div>Unlike Spotify, NekoBeat is free forever, uses under 150MB RAM (vs 300-500MB), has a 10-band hardware equalizer, and lets you stream from YouTube and SoundCloud. However, Spotify's catalog is larger for mainstream music.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>What platforms are supported?</summary>
					<div>Windows 10/11 is available now. macOS, Linux, and Android versions are in development and coming soon.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Is NekoBeat safe to use?</summary>
					<div>NekoBeat is built with Rust and Tauri for memory safety. All code is open-source on GitHub. No tracking, no telemetry, no ads. Your listening history stays on your machine.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Can I use my own audio files?</summary>
					<div>Yes! NekoBeat supports local file playback. You can upload .lrc, .srt, or .vtt files for synchronized lyrics with your own music collection.</div>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>How do I report bugs or request features?</summary>
					<div>Visit our GitHub repository at github.com/nishal21/NekoBeat to open an issue or pull request. We welcome community contributions!</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

